     1вҶ’# Archived project. No maintenance. 
     3вҶ’This project is not maintained anymore and is archived. Feel free to fork and
     4вҶ’make your own changes if needed. For more detail read my blog post: [Taking an indefinite sabbatical from my projects](https://arslan.io/2018/10/09/taking-an-indefinite-sabbatical-from-my-projects/)
     5вҶ’
     6вҶ’Thanks to everyone for their valuable feedback and contributions.
     7вҶ’
     8вҶ’# Structs
    10вҶ’Structs contains various utilities to work with Go (Golang) structs. It was
    11вҶ’initially used by me to convert a struct into a `map[string]interface{}`. With
    12вҶ’time I've added other utilities for structs.  It's basically a high level
    13вҶ’package based on primitives from the reflect package. Feel free to add new
    14вҶ’functions or improve the existing code.
    15вҶ’
    16вҶ’## Install
    18вҶ’```bash
    19вҶ’go get github.com/fatih/structs
    20вҶ’```
    21вҶ’
    22вҶ’## Usage and Examples
    24вҶ’Just like the standard lib `strings`, `bytes` and co packages, `structs` has
    25вҶ’many global functions to manipulate or organize your struct data. Lets define
    26вҶ’and declare a struct:
    27вҶ’
    28вҶ’```go
    29вҶ’type Server struct {
    30вҶ’	Name        string `json:"name,omitempty"`
    31вҶ’	ID          int
    32вҶ’	Enabled     bool
    33вҶ’	users       []string // not exported
    34вҶ’	http.Server          // embedded
    35вҶ’}
    36вҶ’
    37вҶ’server := &Server{
    38вҶ’	Name:    "gopher",
    39вҶ’	ID:      123456,
    40вҶ’	Enabled: true,
    41вҶ’}
    42вҶ’```
    43вҶ’
    44вҶ’```go
    45вҶ’// Convert a struct to a map[string]interface{}
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    74вҶ’### Struct methods
    76вҶ’The structs functions can be also used as independent methods by creating a new
    77вҶ’`*structs.Struct`. This is handy if you want to have more control over the
    78вҶ’structs (such as retrieving a single Field).
    79вҶ’
    80вҶ’```go
    81вҶ’// Create a new struct type:
    82вҶ’s := structs.New(server)
    83вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
    95вҶ’### Field methods
    97вҶ’We can easily examine a single Field for more detail. Below you can see how we
    98вҶ’get and interact with various field methods:
    99вҶ’
   100вҶ’
   101вҶ’```go
   102вҶ’s := structs.New(server)
   103вҶ’
   104вҶ’// Get the Field struct for the "Name" field
